FBIS4-60302 "drnes100_j_94021" FBIS-NES-94-100 Daily Report 24 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Wrapup of Reaction to al-Bid Secession Attempt Noted Wrapup of Reaction to al-Bid Secession Attempt Noted YSP Parliamentary Bloc Urges Unity JN2405143494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 24 May 94 JN2405143494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] A number of the members of the parliamentary bloc representing the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] have issued a statement in which they reiterated their strong and firm adherence to Yemeni unity as the fate of our people, stressing that no individual, group, or political force can encroach on this unity. They condemned the sedition ignited by the rebellious gang of apostasy in the YSP leadership among the sons of the one people. The members of the YSP parliamentary bloc also denounced the secession declaration, affirming its political illegitimacy. They considered this declaration a crime and high treason against our Yemeni people. The YSP parliamentary bloc reiterated their adherence to constitutional legitimacy based on the results of the parliamentary elections held on 27 April 1993.
